{
  "texts": [
    "The need for considering twisted principal bundles (as opposed to a globallydefined free isometric Lie group action) is justified by Proposition 3.7.In Section 4 we restrict ourselves to the case dim B = 2, and prove Theorem B.",
    "We then introduce G-Higgs bundles, discuss the non-abelian Hodge correspondence, and prove Theorem C. The proof of Corollary D is given in Section 4.2.",
    "The cases of dimensions 4 and 5, including the proofs of Corollaries E and F, are discussed in Section 5.In Section 6 we introduce affine expanding solitons, and prove that they must indeed satisfy Ansatz 3.1 (Theorem 6.2).",
    "This, together with the results in Section 3, finishes the proof of Theorem A.",
    "We also characterise the gradient condition (Proposition 6.3), showing in particular that a large class of expanders constructed in this paper are not gradient.The proof of the Einstein extension theorem Theorem G is given in Section 7."
  ]
}